Definition at line 223 of file cb_types.h.

#define cb_EMPTY_ARRAY   (0)

Used when declaring an empty array that does not take up space in a struct.

Example: struct { cb_uint8 payload[cb_EMPTY_ARRAY]; } In some compilers this is empty i.e. payload[]. While in some it requires a zero. I.e. payload[0]; Use this define to get it working for your system.
